      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i><b>The Whisperers</b></i> is a <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1967_in_film" title="1967 in film">1967</a> <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cinema_of_the_United_Kingdom" title="Cinema of the United Kingdom">British</a> <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drama_film" title="Drama film">drama film</a> directed by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bryan_Forbes" title="Bryan Forbes">Bryan Forbes</a>. It is based on the 1961 novel by <a class="external" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Robert_Nicolson&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" title="Robert Nicolson (page does not exist)">Robert Nicolson</a>.</p>
      <h2 xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"> <span class="mw-headline" id="Plot">Plot</span></h2>
      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><i>The Whisperers</i> tells the story of an impoverished old woman living alone in a seedy apartment who enjoys a rich fantasy life as an heiress. When she discovers stolen money hidden by her son, she believes her fantasy has come true.</p>
